code_changes.content:
{
  "files": [
    {
      "repo": "sg-evals/expressjs-express",
      "path": "package.json",
      "version": "0.7.1"
    }
  ],
  "text": "A security audit across the Node.js web stack identified one runtime dependency on the vulnerable `cookie` package. The Express.js web framework (version 4.21.1) declares `cookie` version 0.7.1 as a direct dependency in its package.json file. This version is vulnerable to CVE-2024-47764, which allows attackers to bypass cookie security controls through crafted HTTP requests. The Node.js runtime (v22.13.0), Lodash utility library, and Prisma ORM do not declare `cookie` as a direct runtime dependency. Prisma's client package includes `cookie-es` in devDependencies, but this is a different package. Immediate remediation should upgrade Express's `cookie` dependency to version 0.7.0 or later."
}

